comments.body:
bq. the exact same test class, with only the name changed, doesn't fail using the same seed.

This is by design, Hoss. The input seed for a class is mangled with class name. See LuceneTestCase's header:
{code}
@SeedDecorators({MixWithSuiteName.class}) // See LUCENE-3995 for rationale.
{code}
and refer to LUCENE-3995 for  more.

In general, the seed is valid for repros only if nothing changes at the code level. It's much like uncertainty principle -- if you change the tiniest bit that affects randomization the execution paths may (and should) change (a lot).
